Author:  BURCHFIELD
Vol / Page:  196
Edition:
Quote:  trailer-sailer Chiefly N.Z. & Austral. Also without hyphen. [f. TRAILER sb. 6b + SAILER 2b.] A sailing vessel, usu. one up to 8 metres in length, that can be carried on a motor-vehicle trailer. Usu. with a centreboard or retractable keel.
